Questions:
Which of the following is considered the experimental component of the FearLess study for patients with glioma?
A) Regular neuropsychological evaluations and recommendations from Dr. Loughan as part of usual care;
B) Completion of online surveys about fear of cancer recurrence, mood, and quality of life;
C) Accessing treatment for mental health or cognitive concerns related to diagnosis and treatment;
D) Participation in weekly Zoom sessions with a study clinician as part of the FearLess intervention program.

Correct answer: D

If you choose not to participate in the FearLess intervention program, what standard care options are available to you at the clinic?
A) You will receive a specialized yoga program tailored to your fitness level; 
B) You will have access to regular neuropsychological evaluations and recommendations from Dr. Loughan; 
C) You will be enrolled in an alternative experimental drug trial; 
D) You will be provided with a series of self-help books on coping with brain tumors.

Correct answer: B

If you have any questions or concerns about your rights as a participant in the FearLess study, whom should you contact?

A) The Principal Investigator, Dr. Ashlee Loughan;
B) Virginia Commonwealth University Office of Research;
C) Your personal physician;
D) The Department of Health and Human Services (DHHS).

Correct answer: B) Virginia Commonwealth University Office of Research;
